Germany’s key DAX index on Wednesday fell sharply following other markets down on concerns over the spreading coronavirus epidemic and recovered before midday to trade 1.4 per cent down. The index of 30 German blue-chips hit a low of 12,405, down 3.0 per cent down on the day and the lowest level since mid-October in 2019.It later recovered to levels above 12,600. The index was as high as 13,789 few days ago. The EuroStoxx 50 of leading eurozone shares fell by 2.2 per cent to 3,569.51. According to Commerzbank analyst, Christoph Geyer, said “Fear was waving its sceptre on international stock exchanges”. Market players were extremely sensitive when the long-term effects of an event could not be accurately assessed. (dpa/NAN) 